      <!--HTML -->

      <a id="html"></a>
      <div class="section_Menu">
        <div class="title_section">
          <h3>HTML</h3>
          <em>Controls the Structure</em><br>
          <em><a href="https://validator.w3.org/#validate_by_input" class="verify">Verify html</a></em>
        </div>
        <div class="title_concept"> 
          Markup
        </div> 
        <div class="concept"> 
          &lt;NAME&gt;&lt;/NAME&gt;
        </div>
          <div class="inlinebox"> <!-- Use the Div to put each block next to each other-->
            <div class="title_concept"> 
              Inline
            </div>
            <div class="concept">
              <p>
                - Bold: &lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt; <br>
               - Italic: &lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt; <br>
               - Space: &lt;br&gt; <br>
                - Span: &lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;<br>
               - strong: &lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;<br> 
                - Comments: &lt;!-- TEXT --&gt;<br>
                - All braquets <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element#Content_sectioning">here</a>
              </p>
            </div> 
          </div>
         <div class="blockbox">
          <div class="title_concept">
            Block
          </div> 
          <div class="concept">
            <p>
              <em>(Blocks makes an invisible box with Height and Width)</em>
            </p>
            <p>
              - Paragraph: &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; <br>
              - Div: &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; <br>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="title_concept">
          Attributes
        </div>
        <div class="concept">
          <p>
            <em>Attributes have the following structure: &lt;tag ATTR="Value"> Content &lt;/tag></em>
          </P> 
          <p>
            - Anchor: &lt;a href="URL"&gt;Text&lt;/a&gt; <br>
            - Image: &lt;img src="URL" alt="TEXT"&gt; <br>
            - Form: &lt;form&gt;&lt;/form&gt;<br>
            <a href="http://www.w3schools.com/html/html_attributes.asp">More...</a>
           </p>
        </div>
        <div class="title_concept">
          Squeleton for webpage
        </div>
        <div class="concept">
          <p>
            <em>(In HTML5 the Doctype is simplified to to HTML)</em>
          </p> 
          <code> <!-- <menu></menu> doesn't seem to work on Chrome  (It makes the code diseaper)--> 
            &lt;!DOCTYPE HTML&gt;<br>
            &lt;html&gt;<br>
            &lt;head&gt;<br>
            &lt;title&gt;Title!&lt;/title&gt;<br>
            &lt;style type="text/css"&gt;&lt;/style&gt;
            &lt;/head&gt;<br>
            &lt;body&gt;<br>
            &lt;b&gt;Content&lt;/b&gt;<br>
            &lt;/body&gt;<br>
            &lt;/html&gt;<br>
            In the body everything is part of a box. 
          </code>
          <p>For HTML element reference <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element#Content_sectioning">Here</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="title_concept">
          Images
        </div>
        <div class="concept">
          <p>
            Images should have the src and alt 
          </p>  
        </div>    
        <div class="title_concept">
          Domain Object Model
        </div>
        <div class="concept">
          <p>
            Most web Browser use an internal Model similar to the DOM = DOM Tree <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Document_Object_Model">Source</a> <br> 
            DOM Tree help programmer navigate through the document. <br> 
            Each element can contain other elements making it easier to find what is needed<br>
            <img src="images/HTMLDOMTree.png" alt="Example of DOM Tree" id="dom">
          </p>  
        </div>   
       </div>

      <!-- CSS -->

      <a id="css"></a>
      <div class="section_Menu">
        <div class="title_section">
        <h3>CSS</h3>
        <em>Controls how it looks</em><br>
        <em><a href="http://jigsaw.w3.org/css-validator/#validate_by_input" class="verify">Verify css</a></em>
        </div> 
        <div class="title_concept">
        Info
        </div>
        <div class="concept"> 
          <p>    
            - Use .NAMEOFCLASS OR #NAMEFORID { } <br>
            -  specific rule rules <br> 
            - for normalizing CSS across Browers use <a href="http://necolas.github.io/normalize.css/">normalize.css</a> <br>
            - For CSS <a href="https://css-tricks.com/how-css-selectors-work/">Tricks</a><br>
            - CSS References <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Reference">Here</a><br> 
            - CLASS = group of element that can be styled together - use .CLASSNAME <br>
            - ID = Unique Identifier that uniquely identifies and element - use #IDNAME<br>
            - Tag name - use the tag name to appply on all tags <br>
            - comments in CSS are /* */. <br>
            - Indentation is Tag > . > # <br>
            - Color CSS : <a href="http://www.w3schools.com/cssref/css_colornames.asp">Here</a>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="title_concept">
          Box Set up
        </div>
        <div class="concept">
          <p>
            Box are made respectively of: Margin - Border - Padding - Content. going from outside to inside <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=14v=jlp8uLzt16E">Example</a><br> 
            or <a href="http://assignments.udacity-extras.appspot.com/courses/html-css/samples/box-model.html">here</a><br>
            Margin has no background
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="title_concept">
          CCS Tricks
        </div>
        <div class="concept">
          <h5>Unifomizing the boxes</h5>
          <p>
          *{<br>
            -webkit-box-sizing:border-box;<br>
            -moz-box-sizing: border-box;<br>
            -ms-box-sizing: border-box;<br>
            box-sizing: border-box;<br>
          }
          </p>
          <h5>Framwork CSS visual</h5>
          <p>
            * { 
            margin: 8px; <br>
            border: red solid 2px; <br>
            background-color: rgbe(0,0,0,0,15); <br>
          }
          </p> 
        </div>
        <div class="title_concept">
          Flex Boxes - Gets the boxes to appear next to each other
        </div>
        <div class="concept">
          <p>
            element.style { <br>
            display:flex <br>
            display: -webkit-flex;<br>
            } <br>
            <a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/">More Info</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
